"The driver of the car sped off soon after the accident, leaving the rider in a pool of blood," one witness said.Mwea East police boss Daniel Kavita said his officers rushed to the scene immediately they received the report of the accident.
He said the body was taken to Kerugoya Referral Hospital mortuary, pending investigations into the incident.Mr Kavita said the driver of the car was being pursued.
Mr Kavita said the car was identified by witnesses and police will not rest until the owner is seized.





In another accident, one person died while 19 others were seriously injured on New Year's day in Ena Village in Embu County.
The accident occurred at about 8am today (Friday) when a bus rolled, killing the driver.
According to witnesses, the driver of the Meru-bound Kensilver bus was trying to avoid a head-on collision with an oncoming vehicle when the bus rolled.
Survivors were taken to Embu and Runyenjes hospitals.
The accident caused a major traffic jam as residents blocked the road as they rescued the survivors, some of whom suffered leg and hand fractures.
Most of those wounded were going home for New Year celebrations.
County police commander Daniel Rukunga said the driver's body was taken to Embu Referral Hospital mortuary. The bus wreckage was towed to the local police station.



